Akure – Adekunle Ajasin University, Akungba-Akoko, Ondo State has been granted full accreditation status for five new courses by the National Universities Commission (NUC). A document signed by the Director of Accreditation of the Commission, Dr. Maryam Sali, and addressed to the varsity, listed Fisheries and Aquaculture, Performing Arts, Mathematics, Microbiology, and Mass Communication as the courses that were fully accredited. A statement by the spokesman to the university, Mr. Victor Akinpelu and made available to newsmen in Akure, the state capital, revealed that the varsity regulatory body between October and November 2021 carried out periodic accreditation exercises of the courses in the institution and others across the nation. In his reaction to the development, the AAUA Vice-Chancellor, Prof. Olugbenga Ige, appreciated the efforts of the NUC at ensuring quality and high standard of courses in the nation’s varsities. He also appreciated the Visitor to the University and Governor of Ondo State, Arakunrin Oluwarotimi Akeredolu, for his special support for the institution on the accreditation exercise.